params.limitWei: The spend limit of the key (in wei)
params.publicKey: The public key of the key

params.calls: The encoded calls to execute (plaintext if nonce is 0, ciphertext otherwise)
params.idx: The index of the key to use

returns._0: The domain separator used for EIP-712 typed data signing

multiSend(bytes).details: Sends multiple transactions and reverts all if one fails.

params.transactions: Encoded transactions. Each transaction is encoded as a packed bytes of                     operation has to be uint8(0) in this version (=> 1 byte),                     to as a address (=> 20 bytes),                     value as a uint256 (=> 32 bytes),                     data length as a uint256 (=> 32 bytes),                     data as bytes.                     see abi.encodePacked for more information on packed encoding

params.publicKey: The public key of the key

verifyAndConsumeNonce(uint32,bytes,bytes.details: This function is used to verify a signature and consume the nonce of a keyThis is primarily for external contracts to verify signatures and consume nonces to avoid replay attacks, for use cases like signed reads using passkeys/session keys.

returns._0: valid True if the signature is valid

getKeyIndex(uint8,bytes).notice: Returns the index of a key

getKeyNonce(uint32).notice: Returns the nonce of a key

multiSend(bytes).notice: The code is for most part the same as the normal MultiSend (to keep compatibility),         but reverts if a transaction tries to use a delegatecall.This method is payable as delegatecalls keep the msg.value from the previous call         If the calling method (e.g. execTransaction) received ETH this would revert otherwise

verifyAndConsumeNonce(uint32,bytes,bytes.notice: Verifies a signature and consumes the nonce
